WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.464
Open the Inventory menu.

p02
00:00:02.197 --> 00:00:06.092
Six pages line the sidebar, and every one of them reads the same way.

p03
00:00:06.507 --> 00:00:08.292
A row of headline numbers up top.

p04
00:00:08.620 --> 00:00:09.649
Three cards under it.

p05
00:00:09.872 --> 00:00:11.299
Then a searchable list.

p06
00:00:12.091 --> 00:00:14.062
Item detail is its own lesson.

p07
00:00:14.408 --> 00:00:16.190
Today we walk the other five.

p08
00:00:16.640 --> 00:00:18.511
Start with Inventory Batches.

p09
00:00:18.865 --> 00:00:20.242
This is your receiving log.

p10
00:00:20.635 --> 00:00:23.137
The tiles up top count how many batches arrived, how many are still open, and what they cost.

p11
00:00:23.388 --> 00:00:25.709
But the column that earns its keep is Reference.

p12
00:00:26.009 --> 00:00:28.439
It carries the purchase order each batch filled,

p13
00:00:28.815 --> 00:00:34.618
so a receipt on screen ties straight back to the order behind it.

p14
00:00:34.986 --> 00:00:38.534
When someone asks what actually landed on a P-O, you look here.

p15
00:00:38.960 --> 00:00:40.249
Now Adjustments.

p16
00:00:40.919 --> 00:00:46.246
Every stock correction the network makes lands here, split into positives and negatives.

p17
00:00:46.876 --> 00:00:51.224
What makes the page useful in support is that a correction is never anonymous.

p18
00:00:51.644 --> 00:00:56.241
Each row names the location, the ticket, the shift, and the cashier behind it.

p19
00:00:56.614 --> 00:00:59.214
So a write-off isn't just a dollar figure.

p20
00:00:59.564 --> 00:01:02.177
It's a person and a moment you can go ask about.

p21
00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:04.767
Vendors is the supplier directory.

p22
00:01:05.499 --> 00:01:09.285
Account number, company, contact, address, phone.

p23
00:01:09.756 --> 00:01:12.835
When an order runs late or a chemical shipment comes up short,

p24
00:01:13.089 --> 00:01:15.675
this is the page that hands you the name and number to call.

p25
00:01:16.004 --> 00:01:18.677
The tile up top counts three open P-Os.

p26
00:01:19.001 --> 00:01:22.700
That's the same figure waiting for you one page over, on Purchase Orders.

p27
00:01:23.188 --> 00:01:24.668
Chemicals and Supplies.

p28
00:01:25.272 --> 00:01:28.531
For a field tech, this is the page that answers the call.

p29
00:01:29.118 --> 00:01:32.063
Read Stock Level against Par, the reorder point,

p30
00:01:32.327 --> 00:01:34.606
and the gap tells you how deep the hole is.

p31
00:01:35.180 --> 00:01:38.085
The Status chip says the same thing in one word:

p32
00:01:38.481 --> 00:01:39.976
In Stock, Low Stock, Critical, or Out of Stock.

p33
00:01:40.241 --> 00:01:41.939
When an alert fires that a tank is low, you come here, confirm the level,

p34
00:01:42.459 --> 00:01:49.020
and grab the supplier from the same row.

p35
00:01:49.440 --> 00:01:50.351
Last page: Purchase Orders.

p36
00:01:50.698 --> 00:01:51.688
This is the order pipeline.

p37
00:01:52.304 --> 00:01:53.948
The tiles split it by stage: open, pending approval, in transit.

p38
00:01:54.817 --> 00:01:59.366
The list adds the supplier, the site, the money, and the two dates a caller cares about,

p39
00:02:00.129 --> 00:02:05.081
when it was created and when it's expected.

p40
00:02:05.452 --> 00:02:13.600
The Status chip tells you whether it's still waiting on a signoff, riding on a truck, or done.

p41
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:15.940
Every order row has a View button.

p42
00:02:16.410 --> 00:02:19.069
Click it and a quick-look slides in over the list.

p43
00:02:19.625 --> 00:02:23.405
In the demo it opens on a sample record, so we won't read fields off it.

p44
00:02:24.256 --> 00:02:26.990
Open Full Detail is the door to the real order.

p45
00:02:27.543 --> 00:02:29.440
Close the peek, and nothing moves.

p46
00:02:29.840 --> 00:02:31.788
Five pages, one sidebar.

p47
00:02:32.363 --> 00:02:35.443
Batches for what came in and which P-O it filled.

p48
00:02:36.017 --> 00:02:38.414
Adjustments for who changed a count and why.

p49
00:02:39.085 --> 00:02:40.524
Vendors for who to call.

p50
00:02:41.077 --> 00:02:43.371
Chemicals and Supplies for what's running low.

p51
00:02:43.882 --> 00:02:45.638
Purchase Orders for what's on the way.

p52
00:02:46.137 --> 00:02:50.384
Same layout every time, so once you can read one, you can read all six.

